    {
        "id": 1676728125,
        "number": 48,
        "title": "Tons of errors - Solution ",
        "state": "open",
        "created_at": "2023-04-20T13:27:20Z",
        "updated_at": "2023-04-20T13:27:20Z",
        "closed_at": null,
        "author": "Jamiex64",
        "comments": 0,
        "labels": [],
        "assignees": [],
        "locked": false,
        "body": "I cannot be certain but I fixed mine by manually downloading the log4net from https://logging.apache.org/log4net/download_log4net.html\r\n\r\nI put this in C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft SDKs\\NuGetPackages and I did the following:\r\n\r\nRight click the Solution in the Solution Explorer and click on \"Manage Nuget Packages for Solution..\"\r\nThere should be a restoration button where you can restore the packages and then you should be able to run your solution.\r\n\r\nThis might have been removed with the recent log4j and log4net vulnerabilities identified.  I fixed it this way.",
        "url": "https://github.com/julianperrott/FishingFun/issues/48"
    },
